-- American Media Wins Leave to Use $65.5 Million in Reorganization
-- B y   D o n a l d   J e f f r e y
-- 2010-12-06T20:24:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/national-enquirer-owner-wins-right-to-use-65-5-million-cash-in-bankruptcy.html
American Media Inc. won Bankruptcy
Court authorization to use up to $65.5 million in cash for
operations and expenses in its Chapter 11 reorganization.  The publisher of the National Enquirer and Star magazine
expects to exit court protection by the end of this year,
according to its lawyers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donald Jeffrey in New York at 
